resourceAbstractObject.default: Data from the 'Plant communities observatory' (OCOVE): Observation of plant and fungal communities: measurement of the environment (temperature, rain, minerals), individual monitoring, taxonomic identification, molecular data, etc.. This observatory is part of the Montpellier Research Observatory of Environment (OSU OREME, oreme.org). It consists in different observing tasks: Dynamics of plant in urban environment ; Forest recruitment and pastoralism ; Fungal communities ; Impact of tree hedges on air quality ; Orchids ; Vegetation dynamics and climate.
